I think HWT is excellent especially for tactile learners.

One thing that helps children with writing is using short pencils
(golf pencils work well) or using pencil grips that are sold in
various places.  With crayons too, it is actually helpful to break
them into a shorter piece.  The shorter writing utensils encourage the
proper grip and make it easier to control the pencil or crayon.

Another activity that is fun for kids that helps fine motor control is
having you write a letter or sentence in chalk on a chalkboard and
having the child erase it using water on his finger.  Promotes
learning the writing by making the letter disappear.

